## Agent Teams

This project is configured for Claude Code's native agent teams feature.

### Enabling
Agent teams are enabled via `CLAUDE_CODE_EXPERIMENTAL_AGENT_TEAMS=1` (pre-configured in `.claude/settings.json`).

### Display Modes
Configure `teammateMode` in settings:
- `in-process` — Teammates run in the same terminal (navigate with Shift+Up/Down)
- `tmux` — Each teammate gets its own pane (requires tmux or iTerm2)
- `auto` (default) — Automatically chooses based on environment

### Delegate Mode
Press `Shift+Tab` to toggle the team lead into delegation-only mode. In this mode, the lead coordinates via task list and mailbox only — no direct implementation.

### Custom Subagents
Define specialized teammates in `.claude/agents/`:
- `researcher.md` — Explores codebase, reads docs, answers questions (model: opus)
- `implementer.md` — Writes code, runs tests, makes edits (model: sonnet)
- `reviewer.md` — Reviews changes, checks conventions, validates (model: sonnet)
- Create your own: copy `_template.md` and customize

### Teammate Communication
- **Mailbox**: Point-to-point or broadcast messages between teammates
- **Shared Task List**: Work queue with status tracking and dependencies
- **Idle Notifications**: Automatic alerts when teammates finish

### When to Use Teams vs. Solo

| Scenario | Approach |
|----------|----------|
| Single-focus feature work | Solo Claude session |
| Large feature with parallel tasks | Agent team with task delegation |
| Code review while implementing | Reviewer teammate in parallel |
| Research + implementation | Researcher gathers context, implementer builds |

### Quality Hooks
- `TeammateIdle` — Fires when a teammate finishes; validate output before reassigning
- `TaskCompleted` — Fires when a task is marked complete; exit code 2 blocks completion

See `docs/agent-teams-guide.md` for the comprehensive reference.

